Why not the same way you&#39;re getting the `$ip`?
```php
Broadcast::channel(&#39;chat&#39;, function ($user) {
        $ip = Request::ip();
        if (auth()-&gt;check()) { 
            $time = now(); // Here
            return [
                &#39;id&#39; =&gt; $user-&gt;id,
                &#39;ip&#39; =&gt; $ip,
                &#39;name&#39; =&gt; $user-&gt;name,
                &#39;joined&#39; =&gt; $time,
            ];
        }
    });
```
[now()](https://laravel.com/docs/helpers#method-now) helper function returns a Carbon instance with the current time

From the [docs](https://laravel.com/docs/helpers#method-now)

The `now` function creates a new `Illuminate\Support\Carbon` instance for the current time:
```php
$now = now();
```

